					<description><![CDATA[In reply to &lt;a href=&quot;https://wordcounter.net/blog/2016/08/29/102266_is-writing-art.html#comments/8989&quot;&gt;Steph Rolland&lt;/a&gt;.

Yes, the definition of &quot;art&quot; is a bit broad for my liking in this article. I still believe writing is an art, but I don&#039;t believe all types of writing should be considered art. For example, business writing is business writing. Someone might be good at it, but it isn&#039;t artful writing except possibly in the subset of business writing. Nobody would ever confuse a business proposal as written art.]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>In reply to <a href="https://wordcounter.net/blog/2016/08/29/102266_is-writing-art.html#comments/8989">Steph Rolland</a>.</p>
<p>Yes, the definition of &#8220;art&#8221; is a bit broad for my liking in this article. I still believe writing is an art, but I don&#8217;t believe all types of writing should be considered art. For example, business writing is business writing. Someone might be good at it, but it isn&#8217;t artful writing except possibly in the subset of business writing. Nobody would ever confuse a business proposal as written art.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
		
