					<description><![CDATA[In reply to &lt;a href=&quot;https://wordcounter.net/blog/2016/08/29/102266_is-writing-art.html#comments/8887&quot;&gt;artist&lt;/a&gt;.

I don&#039;t know. I would classify a writing more as a skill than as an art. I think of art as being something that is done to celebrate somebody&#039;s creativity whereas writing is a daily skill. Of course, there are times when people are writing creatively and this could be considered as art. But the day-to-day writing that everybody does is more of a skilled than an art in my opinion.]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>In reply to <a href="https://wordcounter.net/blog/2016/08/29/102266_is-writing-art.html#comments/8887">artist</a>.</p>
<p>I don&#8217;t know. I would classify a writing more as a skill than as an art. I think of art as being something that is done to celebrate somebody&#8217;s creativity whereas writing is a daily skill. Of course, there are times when people are writing creatively and this could be considered as art. But the day-to-day writing that everybody does is more of a skilled than an art in my opinion.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
		
