					<description><![CDATA[I&#039;m not sure I really like this explanation as the definition given means that everything and everything is an art. That&#039;s not really addressing the question in hand which most people reading this are asking -- is writing an art like painting and other activities usually associated with art. Why isn&#039;t writing thought of in this way? That&#039;s really the question that this article should address.]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>I&#8217;m not sure I really like this explanation as the definition given means that everything and everything is an art. That&#8217;s not really addressing the question in hand which most people reading this are asking &#8212; is writing an art like painting and other activities usually associated with art. Why isn&#8217;t writing thought of in this way? That&#8217;s really the question that this article should address.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
		
